  "body": "The do-while loop in question is of the following form:\r\n```\r\ndo {\r\n  // stuff\r\n  break;\r\n}\r\nwhile (true);\r\n```\r\nAs long as `// stuff` doesn't have any `break` or `continue` statements then this is syntactically equivalent to:\r\n```\r\n// stuff\r\n```\r\nIn fact there is one `break`, which can be rewritten as an if-else clause as I've done here.\r\n\r\nMaybe I'm missing something? Absent of some future design or larger purpose I'm not aware of, it seems like the loop is serving no purpose. This PR removes it.",
